[1] National update
Date: Wed 21 Feb 2018 17:15
Source: Secretariat of Health Surveillance, Ministry of Health [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
http://portalms.saude.gov.br/noticias/agencia-saude/42599-ministerio-da-saude-atualiza-casos-de-febre-amarela-7


Brazil confirmed 545 cases and 164 deaths in the period [Sat 1 Jul 2017 - Tue 20 Feb 2018]. During the same period of last year [2016 - 2017] there were 557 confirmed cases and 178 deaths.

This [Wed 21 Feb 2018] they updated the information sent in by the state secretariats of health concerning the yellow fever situation in the country. In the monitoring period (Sat 1 Jul 2017 - Tue 20 Feb 2018) there were 545 confirmed cases of yellow fever in the country, of which 164 were deaths. In total, there were 1773 reported suspected cases, of which 685 were discarded and 422 remain under investigation during this period. Last year, from July 2016 - 20 Feb 2017, there were 557 confirmed cases and 178 confirmed deaths. The yellow fever reports indicate, since last year, the seasonality of the disease that shows the majority of cases occur in summer. Thus, the period of analysis is considered to be 1 July to 30 June of each year.

Campaign
The Ministry of Health underscores the importance of vaccination of the populations in the states of Rio de Janeiro and Sao Paulo during the campaign against yellow fever. Preliminary data from the states of Rio de Janeiro and Sao Paulo state that, up to this [Tue 19 Feb 2018], 5.1 million people were vaccinated, 4.7 million with fractionated doses and 422 600 with complete doses. The number corresponds to 25.2 percent of the expected intended public in the Southeast. The recommendation is that these states continue vaccinating until hitting high coverage. The state of Bahia initiated a campaign in 8 municipalities this [Tue 19 Feb 2018].

In order to help the states and municipalities carry out the campaign, the Ministry of Health allocated R54 million [USD 16 610 000] to the states. Of this total, R15.8 million [USD 4 860 000] for Sao Paulo, R30 million [USD 9 230 000] for Rio de Janeiro and R8.2 million [USD 2 520 000] for Bahia. To attend exclusively to the fractionation campaign, the Ministry of Health distributed 19.4 million doses of the yellow fever vaccine to the states of Rio de Janeiro (4.7 million doses) and Sao Paulo (10 million). Also, 15 million syringes were sent to the states, with 5.2 million to Rio de Janeiro, 500 000 to Bahia and 9.3 million to Sao Paulo.

